- Well, there's something up

13:32.854 --> 13:34.648
with these corporate farmers
out here.

13:34.689 --> 13:37.067
I mean, they seem
to be all doing fine.

13:37.108 --> 13:38.985
And I don't know, we're three
years into a drought,

13:39.027 --> 13:41.363
and there can't be
that much groundwater left.

13:41.404 --> 13:42.614
I think it may
have something to do

13:42.656 --> 13:44.241
with Bobbi's death.

13:44.282 --> 13:46.368
Anyhow, uh, can you get me
Blackwood County

13:46.409 --> 13:48.245
Water Board's address, please?

13:48.286 --> 13:49.454
Uh, you got it.
I'll text you, okay?

13:49.496 --> 13:50.830
All right, I'll call you later.

13:50.872 --> 13:53.833
- Bye.
- All right, bye.

13:53.875 --> 13:57.045
Um, hi. Um, you know,
I was thinking,

13:57.087 --> 13:59.214
would you like,
would you like a top coat?

13:59.256 --> 14:01.216
I-I could just, like,
do a quick topper.

14:01.258 --> 14:03.885
- The fuck I would, no.
- (GASPS)

14:03.927 --> 14:05.804
I love your earrings.

14:05.845 --> 14:08.306
My great aunt had some just like
that, and she's got dementia

14:08.348 --> 14:10.475
