24:26.465 --> 24:27.925
Why don't you
set us up over here?

24:27.967 --> 24:29.510
BILLY: Yeah, just some kind of
bourbon, I don't care.

24:29.552 --> 24:31.721
BLACKWOOD:
Yeah, me, too. Yeah...

24:31.762 --> 24:34.807
What happened to Bobbi Bennett,

24:34.849 --> 24:38.477
- it was tragic.
- Yeah, yeah, it sure was.

24:38.519 --> 24:40.688
Yeah, Gene sunk his nest egg
into that place.

24:40.730 --> 24:42.106
It's bone-dry now.

24:42.148 --> 24:46.444
Well, I just had to rip out
10,000 acres of almond trees

24:46.485 --> 24:49.071
myself this past year. It hurt.

24:49.113 --> 24:51.365
- Cost me a pretty penny.
- Mm.

24:51.407 --> 24:53.409
Well, I've been driving
around here, it looks to me

24:53.451 --> 24:55.912
like you and a couple others are
still doing pretty well, though.

24:55.953 --> 24:57.955
<i>♪ I just dropped in to see... ♪</i>

24:57.997 --> 25:01.417
Drought does not play favorites.

25:01.459 --> 25:05.504
And Gene, his sinkhole,
they call it subsidence.

25:05.546 --> 25:08.883
It's just part of the gamble
of farming in California.

25:08.925 --> 25:11.052
The whole damn county
is sinking.

25:11.093 --> 25:13.888
Well, why did you offer
to buy Gene's land?

25:13.930 --> 25:15.681
Well, I feel bad for the guy.

25:15.723 --> 25:17.725
- Isn't it worthless?
- Well, maybe to him,

25:17.767 --> 25:19.310
but not to me.

25:19.352 --> 25:22.396
Well, it must be a hell of a lot
easier to weather a drought

25:22.438 --> 25:24.065
when your name is Blackwood
in Blackwood County,

25:24.106 --> 25:26.317
and you happen to be the
president of the water board.

25:26.359 --> 25:27.735
Yeah, I'm sure

25:27.777 --> 25:30.238
it looks like that way from the
outside looking in, doesn't it?

25:30.279 --> 25:31.906
Like the deck's
stacked in my favor.

25:31.948 --> 25:34.242
- Mm.
- I mean, the water board

25:34.283 --> 25:37.745
is literally under my roof,

25:37.787 --> 25:39.747
but it's free rent for them.

25:39.789 --> 25:42.708
And as far as being president,
well, that just...

25:42.750 --> 25:45.294
It's an unpaid job,
nobody wants to do it,

25:45.336 --> 25:47.213
and that's what the name
Blackwood gets you.

25:47.255 --> 25:48.839
Hmm.

25:48.881 --> 25:51.175
So, you're saying that,
in Gene's case,

25:51.217 --> 25:53.177
it's just bad luck?

25:55.179 --> 25:57.932
We all feel terrible
about what happened to Bobbi.

25:57.974 --> 25:59.517
Now, who's we?

25:59.558 --> 26:02.687
Us, the farmers,
the ranchers around here.

26:02.728 --> 26:04.272
They're just like me.

26:04.313 --> 26:07.900
The land's been in their
families for generations and...

26:07.942 --> 26:09.986
everybody's had their turn
on the shitter.

26:10.027 --> 26:11.570
Mm. Now it's Gene's turn.

26:11.612 --> 26:14.657
(SIGHS)
You got to understand something.

26:14.699 --> 26:16.492
Right where you're
standing right now,

26:16.534 --> 26:19.453
100 years ago,
there wasn't a drop of water

26:19.495 --> 26:22.123
for as far as you could travel
in a wagon in a day.

26:22.164 --> 26:25.835
Now, can you imagine the will
of consciousness it took

26:25.876 --> 26:28.754
to rewrite God's plan
and to bring all that water

26:28.796 --> 26:30.548
from way up north

26:30.589 --> 26:34.427
and deliver it all the way down
here to this valley,

26:34.468 --> 26:37.763
so that our crops
can feed the world.

26:37.805 --> 26:39.307
And that was one man.

26:39.348 --> 26:42.018
One man with the grit

26:42.059 --> 26:45.229
and the balls to lock horns

26:45.271 --> 26:48.274
with Mother Nature and win.

26:48.316 --> 26:50.776
And that's the kind of soul
you need to farm this land.

26:50.818 --> 26:53.154
(CHUCKLES): I'm just gonna take
a wild stab at this,

26:53.195 --> 26:55.448
but was the guy's name
Blackwood, by any chance?

26:55.489 --> 26:56.741
It's my grandfather.

26:56.782 --> 26:59.160
- Yeah.
- Look, working this land

26:59.201 --> 27:02.538
is like, um...
being in a relationship.

27:02.580 --> 27:05.750
There's give and take,
and there's trust.

27:05.791 --> 27:08.794
And there's a shitload
of betrayal.

27:11.589 --> 27:13.674
- Gene's just waking up to that.
- Well, till then,

27:13.716 --> 27:15.926
how does the water board
figure into all this?

27:15.968 --> 27:17.219
The water board is there

27:17.261 --> 27:19.430
to insure the quality
of the water

27:19.472 --> 27:22.016
and allocate that water
for generations to come.

27:22.058 --> 27:23.726
Yeah, I-I understand that part,

27:23.768 --> 27:26.020
but the water board controls
the distribution of water.

27:26.062 --> 27:28.022
It looks to me like
you got your hand on the tap.

27:28.064 --> 27:29.774
I'm sorry to interrupt,

27:29.815 --> 27:31.525
but the-the high stakes room
is ready.

27:31.567 --> 27:33.527
Well, I'm gonna
have to go, then.

27:33.569 --> 27:34.945
Sorry about that.

27:34.987 --> 27:36.447
Littlecrow.
He runs the place here,

27:36.489 --> 27:38.032
and he don't let me
hold the game up.

27:38.074 --> 27:39.408
Well, listen,
I'm gonna be here for a while,

27:39.450 --> 27:41.118
so, uh, I can just hang out here

27:41.160 --> 27:42.912
if we meet a little bit later?

27:42.953 --> 27:46.248
Well, tonight's no good,
but you live in L.A.?

27:46.290 --> 27:48.709
- Yeah, Santa Monica.
- I got a place in Encino.

27:48.751 --> 27:50.336
- Yeah?
- Yeah, so...

27:50.378 --> 27:52.213
Tell you what, I'll make sure
you get my address.

27:52.254 --> 27:53.589
You want to stop by
tomorrow night?

27:53.631 --> 27:55.758
- Appreciate it.
- I just love talking about water.

27:55.800 --> 27:57.510
(CHUCKLES):
I bet. All right, then.

27:57.551 --> 27:59.512
- You bet.
- All right. Good to meet you.

27:59.553 --> 28:02.515
<i>♪ And leave you there... ♪</i>

28:02.556 --> 28:05.726
So, you and your wife
have fun here?

28:06.769 --> 28:09.522
Um, I'm-I'm here alone.

28:09.563 --> 28:12.233
Oh. Next time, then.

28:12.274 --> 28:14.902
You know,
we'd love to give your wife

28:14.944 --> 28:17.822
the opportunity to win
her money back. (CHUCKLES)

28:17.863 --> 28:20.491
Oh. (CHUCKLES) You got me
mixed up with somebody else.

28:20.533 --> 28:22.410
Yeah.

28:22.451 --> 28:24.036
No, Mr. McBride.

28:24.078 --> 28:26.330
We have met.

28:26.372 --> 28:29.458
Really?

28:29.500 --> 28:31.085
Where was that?

28:31.127 --> 28:33.212
(SCOFFS)
Well, right here, of course.

28:33.254 --> 28:36.132
